news.title: Property allottees must obtain UAN by August 31: Bhubaneswar development body
news.para: The Bhubaneswar Development Authority mandates all property allottees to obtain a Unique Account Number (UAN) by August 31, aiming to digitize services and enhance transparency. BDA has also made significant strides in its leasehold to freehold conversion program, registering 743 conveyance deeds out of 1,250 applications. The conversion fee is set at 3% of the latest benchmark valuation.

news.title: Property prices to increase in Jharkhand from August 1
news.para: Starting August 1st, property buyers in Ranchi and Jamshedpur (excluding Tata sub-lease areas) will face increased real estate prices. A revision in rates, occurring every two years, will lead to approximately a 10% hike in residential and commercial property costs in Jamshedpur. For instance, flats in Sonari, Jamshedpur will now cost Rs 6,061 per sqft.

news.title: Buildings sealed in Gurugram's Sushant Lok-1 for violations of residential zoning laws
news.para: Gurgaon's Sushant Lok 1 faced a major crackdown by the DTCP due to blatant violations of residential zoning laws. Authorities sealed a crèche plot misused for school classes and dance training, a girls' hostel operating in a residential building, and unauthorized construction in a stilt parking area.

news.title: Top government official to chair meet on Odisha RERA
news.para: A high-level meeting, chaired by Chief Secretary Manoj Ahuja, is scheduled to address key issues concerning the Odisha Real Estate Regulatory Authority (ORERA). Following a leadership change in June, this second meeting will focus on strengthening ORERA's operations.

news.title: Telangana HC warns petitioner for repeatedly challenging building approvals in Hafeezpet
news.para: The Telangana High Court criticized a Hyderabad businessman for contesting the legality of approvals for a residential project in Hafeezpet. The court warned the petitioner against misusing the judicial system. The petitioner alleged irregularities in building approvals and environmental clearances. The court permitted the withdrawal of the petition after the petitioner's counsel apologized.

news.title: Gujarat HC lifts stay on civil prison order against Pacifica Developers, initiates contempt proceedings
news.para: The Gujarat High Court has lifted a stay on the GujRERA order to detain Pacifica Developers' officials, including Rakesh Israni, for failing to hand over a house to a customer and allegedly selling it to another party. The court also initiated contempt proceedings against Israni and other office bearers for making false statements.

news.title: Bombay HC raps EOW for inacion, transfers builder fraud case to crime branch
news.para: The Bombay High Court moved a builder fraud case to the Mumbai Crime Branch. This action followed serious investigative failures by the Economic Offences Wing. Victims alleged a scam exceeding Rs 100 crore. The court criticized EOW's handling, citing inaction and negligence. Concerns arose over frozen accounts and untracked property transactions. The Crime Branch will now investigate the matter further.

news.title: Building materials maker CRH to acquire Eco Material for $2.1 billion
news.para: CRH, a building materials giant, will buy Eco Material Technologies. The deal is worth $2.1 billion. This acquisition expands CRH's North American presence. Eco Material is a supplier of low-carbon cement alternatives. The purchase helps CRH move towards sustainable construction. The transaction is expected to be completed in 2025. CRH will use its cash reserves to fund the deal.

news.title: HeidelbergCement India's profit rises 20.8% to ₹48.23 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: HeidelbergCement India Ltd witnessed a 20.87% surge in net profit, reaching Rs 48.23 crore for the June quarter of FY26, fueled by a robust 12.27% increase in revenue from operations, which amounted to Rs 597.54 crore. The company's sales volume also experienced substantial growth, climbing 10.9% to 1,254 kilo tonnes, contributing to the overall positive financial performance.

news.title: Hongkong Land posts profit of $297 million in H1 2025
news.para: Hongkong Land reports signs of stabilisation in Hong Kong's Central office market. Valuations are steady for the first time since 2018. Vacancy rates in Central declined to 6.9%. Rents are still under pressure. The company reported an underlying profit of $297 million.

news.title: Vadodara civic body gets tough on construction debris dumping in water bodies
news.para: The Vadodara Municipal Corporation (VMC) has issued a stern warning against the illegal dumping of construction waste in the Vishwamitri river and other water bodies. Following concerns raised by the State Human Rights Commission's expert committee, the VMC has initiated a drive to curb this practice. Violators will face action under the Environment (Construction and Demolition) Waste Management Rules, 2025.

news.title: Sri Lotus Developers and Realty raises ₹237 crore from anchor investors
news.para: Sri Lotus Developers and Realty secured ₹237 crore from anchor investors. The IPO opens on Wednesday, July 30, 2025. The company allocated shares to anchor investors at ₹150 per share. Several marquee institutions participated. The IPO includes a fresh issue of shares up to ₹792 crore. A discount is offered to eligible employees. The IPO closes on August 1, 2025.

news.title: Spring House Workspaces launches 28,000 sq ft space in Saket, Delhi
news.para: Spring House Workspaces has expanded its presence in Delhi-NCR with a new 28,000 sq ft center at Southern Park Mall, Saket, offering 450 seats.

news.title: Nilkamal net profit declines 16.47% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Nilkamal reported a 16.47% decrease in net consolidated profit for the quarter ending June 30, 2025, with a profit after tax of ₹15.32 crore. Despite this dip in profit, the company's net consolidated total income grew by 18.83% to ₹886.94 crore. Furthermore, Gautam G. Chakravarti has been appointed as an additional independent director, effective July 29, 2025.

news.title: IIT Indore making 'smart glass' to keep buildings cool in summer and warm in winter
news.para: Indian Institute of Technology Indore is developing a smart glass. This glass uses a special polymer. It can control light and heat using electricity. This technology will help construct eco-friendly buildings. The smart glass changes color quickly. It saves energy by reducing the need for cooling and lighting. Researchers are working with industry partners to produce this glass.

news.title: Incuspaze leases three lakh sq ft office space in Jaipur
news.para: Incuspaze is growing its flexible office space business. The company acquired three lakh sq ft in Jaipur. It is expanding into Bengaluru, Chennai, Mumbai, Pune, Delhi NCR and Lucknow. Incuspaze aims to add two million sq ft by December 2025. The company recently acquired TRIOS Co-working. Incuspaze expects revenue of ₹350–400 crore in FY26. An IPO is planned.

news.title: Aldar Properties posts 24% rise in profit in H1 2025
news.para: Aldar Properties, Abu Dhabi's top developer, saw a profit increase. This rise is due to strong project backlogs and high international interest. Chinese buyers are leading this demand. Sales to Chinese investors have already surpassed last year's total. International buyers now make up a large portion of Aldar's UAE sales. The company will focus on domestic operations in the Emirates.

news.title: Asian Paints net profit dips 5.88% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Asian Paints reported a 5.88% dip in net consolidated profit for Q1 FY26, reaching ₹1,117.05 crore. While domestic decorative paints saw a volume growth of 3.9%, revenue declined by 1.2%. International business performed strongly with 11.1% revenue growth, and the company acquired the remaining stake in White Teak, making it a wholly-owned subsidiary.

news.title: Brigade Group to jointly develop two residential projects in Hyderabad
news.para: Brigade Group is expanding its residential footprint in Hyderabad with joint development agreements for Brigade Citadel 2 and 3 in Moti Nagar. These projects, spanning 10 acres, will offer 405 three and four-bedroom homes. The developments have a total development potential of one million sq ft and an estimated revenue potential exceeding ₹970 crore.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers posts net loss of ₹16.88 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers reported a net consolidated loss after tax of ₹16.88 crore for the quarter ended June 30, 2025, a significant downturn from the ₹6.37 crore profit in the same period last year. The company's net consolidated total income also decreased substantially by 72.37% to ₹96.81 crore in Q1 FY26.
